fields.course: Post Graduate Program (PGP) in Data Science, Big Data and Business Analytics
fields.writeup: A post graduation program in Business analytics and big data which includes an In-depth study, practicals and project development in Machine Leaning, Hadoop eco-system including Apache Spark, Information retrieval, Elastic Search, Natural Language Processing, Data Visualization with Tableau, QlikSense and programming languages like R, Python, Java and Scala.

This degree was primarily focused on subjects such as software, databases, and networking. The BSc degree in IT is awarded for completing a programme of study in the field of software development, software testing, software engineering, web design, databases, programming, computer networking and computer systems.

fields.experience_ul:
• Development of AIML applications at scale with expertise in areas of Data Science, Data Engineering, DevOps and MLOps
  • Led the data engineering effort for the development of a self-service customer genomic analytics (unique and individual purchasing imprint) tool for a Fortune 500 bank with a team of 6

• Developed RuralMet, a product which reduced the operational cost from Rs.24L/year to Rs.1.2L/year. It is an Indian street address parser which can break down and classify an address into Urban/Rural categories according to Census mapping. It was developed to report insurance penetration in rural areas to IRDAI for compliance
  • Developed an AI-backed Geospatial Risk Profiler for Property Underwriting called BAGIC Maps.
  • Developed a generic leads generation tool using Selenium to find prospective tie-ups to upsell insurance
  • Led projects for cross-sell modeling, customer segmentation, report automation, analytical modeling and dashboard creation

• Managed a 6-person cross-functional team to devise and develop a product Eugenie.ai - The product was developed for automated insight discovery, anomaly detection and predictive maintenance, on an architecture of distributed and asynchronous services for big data and near real-time delivery.
  • Contributed with technical thought leadership, product and algorithm development, testing and handling client requirements, engagement and deliveries
  • Implemented an automated and concurrent time-series forecasting engine and unsupervised anomaly detection algorithms
  • Executed high-volume (2500 data points/second) streaming pipelines for IoT data in a distributed architecture
  • Demand Forecasting and Trade Promotion optimization use-cases using effective ML methods
